<item>
            <title>[LU-14057] Quiet innacurate log message on server side</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14057</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a client connects to a target, this establishes a client -&amp;gt; server export connection and a corresponding reverse import connection, from target to client. This reverse import connection adds a &quot;Connection restored at ... &quot; log message even if this is the first connection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reverse imports maintain a target -&amp;gt; client connection which does not support recovery as client don&apos;t run a recovery. At every connection, the reverse import state goes from NEW to RECOVER to FULL which triggers a &lt;tt&gt;Connection restored&lt;/tt&gt; log message, even if this is the first connection from this client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we can simply suppress this log message for reverse import to avoid this noise.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
